1:03:33.246 --> 1:03:35.215
looking out for me
the whole time, weren't you?

1:03:35.248 --> 1:03:36.616
[door opens]

1:03:38.918 --> 1:03:41.421
Sami Brady, you and I are going
to get something straight.

1:03:41.454 --> 1:03:42.989
What now, Nicole?

1:03:43.089 --> 1:03:45.358
I saw you uglying
my husband earlier.

1:03:45.392 --> 1:03:46.693
Uglying, really?

1:03:46.726 --> 1:03:49.329
Yes and you're gonna
stay away from him.

1:03:49.362 --> 1:03:50.597
And while you're at it,

1:03:50.630 --> 1:03:52.799
stay away from my daughter, too.
[door slams]

1:03:52.832 --> 1:03:54.200
EJ: Except she isn't
your daughter, is she, Nicole?

1:03:55.168 --> 1:03:56.302
What?

1:03:56.336 --> 1:03:57.804
What are you
talking about?

1:03:57.837 --> 1:03:59.806
I just had a talk
with Rafe Hernandez.

1:03:59.839 --> 1:04:01.941
The man is a self-righteous
Neanderthal

1:04:02.042 --> 1:04:03.543
but he uncovered
a great injustice.

1:04:05.278 --> 1:04:06.179
What are you saying?

1:04:06.212 --> 1:04:07.580
Samantha.

1:04:08.948 --> 1:04:11.084
Our child didn't die
all those years back.

1:04:13.186 --> 1:04:14.888
Nicole switched the babies.

1:04:14.921 --> 1:04:16.523
What?

1:04:16.556 --> 1:04:18.792
Sydney is your daughter,

1:04:18.825 --> 1:04:20.894
not Nicole's.

1:04:20.927 --> 1:04:22.162
My daughter.

1:04:22.195 --> 1:04:24.731
No, no, that is not true.

1:04:24.764 --> 1:04:26.633
Sydney is my daughter.

1:04:28.902 --> 1:04:30.370
She's my daughter.

1:04:32.072 --> 1:04:33.239
No.

1:04:33.273 --> 1:04:34.441
Oh!

1:04:37.577 --> 1:04:39.412
Say it.

1:04:39.446 --> 1:04:41.815
Sydney...

1:04:41.848 --> 1:04:44.718
is EJ's and my daughter,

1:04:44.751 --> 1:04:46.086
isn't she?

1:04:48.421 --> 1:04:49.356
No.

1:04:49.389 --> 1:04:50.690
Oh!

1:04:50.724 --> 1:04:51.958
Say it, Nicole!

1:04:53.193 --> 1:04:55.362
"She's Sami's child."

1:04:55.395 --> 1:04:57.163
Sydney is mine

1:04:57.197 --> 1:05:00.033
and I'm gonna
make you say it.

1:05:06.106 --> 1:05:07.374
Sydney...

1:05:09.075 --> 1:05:10.043
[sniffles]

1:05:10.043 --> 1:05:11.778
Sydney is yours.

1:05:15.482 --> 1:05:16.649
[gasps]

1:05:18.585 --> 1:05:20.553
[breathing heavily]

1:05:22.555 --> 1:05:23.923
Horton's winding down?

1:05:23.957 --> 1:05:25.425
Is it?

1:05:25.458 --> 1:05:26.960
I barely noticed.

1:05:27.060 --> 1:05:28.361
What do you want to do now?

1:05:29.329 --> 1:05:30.663
We could, uh...

1:05:31.664 --> 1:05:33.333
Go back to my place

1:05:33.366 --> 1:05:36.369
and watch the Griswolds

1:05:36.403 --> 1:05:38.405
or we could
watch Bruce Willis

1:05:38.438 --> 1:05:40.407
kill a bunch of terrorists
in his bare feet.

1:05:42.642 --> 1:05:46.446
I thought "Die Hard"
wasn't Christmas movie.

1:05:46.479 --> 1:05:48.081
You know, I'm starting
to see things

1:05:48.081 --> 1:05:49.482
in a whole new light.

1:05:54.087 --> 1:05:57.157
So, this is...

1:05:57.190 --> 1:05:58.792
Awkward?

1:05:58.825 --> 1:06:00.226
It doesn't have to be.

1:06:00.260 --> 1:06:01.828
Yeah, she's right, you know?

1:06:01.861 --> 1:06:04.030
I-- I think we'll
all be happier this way.

1:06:04.064 --> 1:06:05.465
TRIPP: I mean, we're finally
matched with the person

1:06:05.498 --> 1:06:07.734
we're meant to be with,
don't you think?

1:06:10.070 --> 1:06:11.204
Uh-huh.

1:06:12.272 --> 1:06:13.340
Right, Dupree?

1:06:14.874 --> 1:06:16.343
Yeah, Horton.

1:06:16.376 --> 1:06:17.510
Totally.

1:06:18.878 --> 1:06:21.081
LEO: Hello, Historical
Society guy.

1:06:24.250 --> 1:06:27.053
Mr. Stark, you know you did
a wonderful thing tonight.

1:06:27.053 --> 1:06:29.556
I was pleasantly surprised
to see you in the show.

1:06:29.589 --> 1:06:31.191
Really, why?

1:06:31.224 --> 1:06:32.826
Paulina convinced
somebody from the City

1:06:32.859 --> 1:06:34.627
to approve her plans,
I was worried it was you.

1:06:34.661 --> 1:06:36.062
No, not me.

1:06:36.062 --> 1:06:37.364
Mm.

1:06:37.397 --> 1:06:38.865
I wonder who helped her, then.

1:06:40.800 --> 1:06:43.403
If that wasn't so
humiliating,

1:06:43.436 --> 1:06:45.271
my plans foiled

1:06:45.305 --> 1:06:48.441
by a drag show,
of all things.

1:06:48.475 --> 1:06:50.677
WOMAN: I gave it my best shot.

1:06:50.710 --> 1:06:52.245
I called in all my favors

1:06:52.278 --> 1:06:53.980
to get that variance for you.

1:06:54.080 --> 1:06:56.082
Too bad it was all for nothing.

1:06:56.116 --> 1:06:59.519
Well, at least you don't have
to keep running that stupid inn.

1:06:59.552 --> 1:07:01.021
Not to mention,
I think I've blown

1:07:01.021 --> 1:07:03.723
my one chance
to real happiness.

1:07:06.126 --> 1:07:08.461
Seems I had
you pegged all wrong.

1:07:08.495 --> 1:07:10.430
You and the rest
of the human race.

1:07:10.463 --> 1:07:12.932
Seriously, you should
be proud of yourself.

1:07:13.033 --> 1:07:14.401
You helped to save the town.

1:07:14.434 --> 1:07:16.169
I did, didn't I?

1:07:16.202 --> 1:07:18.738
May I ask, what made you
change your tune?

1:07:20.040 --> 1:07:23.643
Honestly, it was that
passionate speech you gave me

1:07:23.677 --> 1:07:27.414
about tradition and some things
being more important than money.

1:07:27.447 --> 1:07:29.082
I didn't think
you were listening.

1:07:29.115 --> 1:07:30.517
Not listening?

1:07:30.550 --> 1:07:33.720
Honey, I'm gonna needlepoint
that speech into a pillow.

1:07:33.753 --> 1:07:36.056
[laughing]
Well, I'm flattered.

1:07:37.090 --> 1:07:38.224
Somehow you got through to me

1:07:38.258 --> 1:07:40.593
in a way nobody else ever has.

1:07:40.627 --> 1:07:42.228
Can't quite explain why.

1:07:43.296 --> 1:07:44.898
Merry Christmas, Leo.

1:07:54.541 --> 1:07:56.343
This town doesn't deserve you.

1:08:02.449 --> 1:08:04.084
You came here to gloat?

1:08:04.117 --> 1:08:07.821
I came here to invite you
to Christmas brunch.

1:08:07.854 --> 1:08:11.624
Me and Johnny
and Allie and Tripp

1:08:11.658 --> 1:08:14.060
we're calling it
"A Very Swappy Christmas."

1:08:15.161 --> 1:08:17.897
You want me there
after I tried to evict you?

1:08:19.199 --> 1:08:21.701
Well, you're an awful Grinch.

1:08:21.735 --> 1:08:23.803
But you're still my mom.

1:08:23.837 --> 1:08:26.239
And I know there's a great
big heart in there somewhere.

1:08:27.674 --> 1:08:28.708
I love you, baby.

1:08:28.742 --> 1:08:30.310
[chuckles]

1:08:30.343 --> 1:08:31.478
I love you, too, Mama/

1:08:31.511 --> 1:08:33.046
- Oh...
- Merry Christmas.

1:08:33.046 --> 1:08:35.882
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1:08:38.318 --> 1:08:40.053
Did Santa come?

1:08:40.053 --> 1:08:41.621
Is it time to open presents?

1:08:41.654 --> 1:08:42.589
[chuckles]

1:08:42.622 --> 1:08:43.857
Oh, yeah, my darling.

1:08:47.327 --> 1:08:51.064
But we do have a gift for you.

1:08:53.500 --> 1:08:54.868
SYDNEY: Sami?

1:08:54.901 --> 1:08:57.337
What are you doing
in my room?

1:08:57.370 --> 1:08:58.838
Well.

1:09:01.107 --> 1:09:02.676
Sydney...

1:09:02.709 --> 1:09:04.911
your Christmas wish...

1:09:05.011 --> 1:09:06.079
has come true.

1:09:08.314 --> 1:09:09.783
I'm your mommy.

1:09:09.816 --> 1:09:11.785
What?

1:09:11.818 --> 1:09:13.520
You are?

1:09:13.553 --> 1:09:14.888
She is?

1:09:14.921 --> 1:09:15.822
She is.

1:09:17.223 --> 1:09:19.526
Nothing could make me happier.

1:09:19.559 --> 1:09:22.295
I love Christmas, mommy.

1:09:22.328 --> 1:09:23.730
And I love you.

1:09:23.763 --> 1:09:26.232
Oh, sweetheart,
I love you so much.

1:09:28.234 --> 1:09:29.369
[sniffles]

1:09:31.204 --> 1:09:32.405
[laughing]

1:09:36.309 --> 1:09:37.577
- Excuse me.
- Uh, wait.

1:09:41.581 --> 1:09:42.449
Hi.

1:09:42.482 --> 1:09:43.516
Hi.

1:09:45.919 --> 1:09:47.654
I can't stop
thinking about that...

1:09:47.687 --> 1:09:49.656
little performance
you gave last night.

1:09:52.625 --> 1:09:54.961
Well, we've already
established that you...

1:09:55.061 --> 1:09:57.931
like my hard body.

1:09:57.964 --> 1:09:59.666
- I do.
- Hm.

1:09:59.699 --> 1:10:02.802
I do, but it-- no,
it was more what you said.

1:10:02.836 --> 1:10:04.704
Actually, what you wrote.

1:10:04.738 --> 1:10:05.839
And...

1:10:07.307 --> 1:10:09.175
I just want to tell you
that I love you, too.

1:10:12.812 --> 1:10:15.448
- You do?
- I do.

1:10:15.482 --> 1:10:17.150
I mean,
I really, really do.

1:10:18.752 --> 1:10:21.121
And I want to be with you.

1:10:21.154 --> 1:10:22.355
For real.

1:10:23.890 --> 1:10:25.458
If you still have me.

1:10:27.260 --> 1:10:28.695
Oh, God, Kristen.

1:10:41.975 --> 1:10:43.076
Come on.

1:10:43.109 --> 1:10:44.344
[grunts]

1:10:44.377 --> 1:10:46.212
Such a big girl!

1:10:46.246 --> 1:10:48.648
Hold on, let me
get the bed ready.

1:10:48.682 --> 1:10:50.417
Ooh, ooh, ooh.

1:10:50.450 --> 1:10:51.918
Let's take those slippers

1:10:55.288 --> 1:10:57.090
There you go.

1:10:57.123 --> 1:10:58.858
Now...

1:10:58.892 --> 1:11:00.493
You close your eyes

1:11:00.527 --> 1:11:03.063
so that Santa
can deliver your presents.

1:11:04.364 --> 1:11:05.832
And we'll see you
in the morning.

1:11:09.336 --> 1:11:10.503
[sighs]

1:11:16.076 --> 1:11:17.544
[EJ exhales]

1:11:29.422 --> 1:11:30.957
I can't believe it.

1:11:30.990 --> 1:11:33.560
I can't believe
she's really mine.

1:11:33.593 --> 1:11:36.363
She's our child, Samantha.

1:11:38.098 --> 1:11:39.466
I meant to be a family.

1:11:41.801 --> 1:11:45.305
When I fix all this mess
with Nicole,

1:11:45.338 --> 1:11:46.806
maybe you and I can...

1:11:49.676 --> 1:11:52.278
Maybe you and I could...

1:12:11.064 --> 1:12:12.565
What a Christmas.

1:12:15.869 --> 1:12:17.671
And the awful truth came out.

1:12:19.239 --> 1:12:20.407
Oh, God.

1:12:21.408 --> 1:12:23.376
Please, forgive me.

1:12:28.081 --> 1:12:30.183
You know what?
I take that back.

1:12:30.216 --> 1:12:33.286
After what I did to Sydney
and EJ and Sami,

1:12:33.319 --> 1:12:35.088
I don't deserve forgiveness.

1:12:55.475 --> 1:12:57.410
MAN: Everyone
deserves forgiveness.

1:13:03.883 --> 1:13:05.218
[gasps]

1:13:15.495 --> 1:13:16.629
[door opens]

1:13:19.299 --> 1:13:20.567
Oof.

1:13:22.068 --> 1:13:23.069
Oh...

1:13:23.069 --> 1:13:24.270
John?

1:13:27.140 --> 1:13:28.508
Ah, hey.

1:13:31.978 --> 1:13:33.880
Is everything all right?

1:13:40.787 --> 1:13:42.355
Kristen and I we're...

1:13:43.957 --> 1:13:45.558
We're gonna get a divorce.

1:13:46.826 --> 1:13:49.229
Oh.

1:13:49.262 --> 1:13:51.131
I'm so sorry.

1:13:53.967 --> 1:13:55.168
Thank you, Doc.

1:13:58.204 --> 1:13:59.673
Doc.

1:14:02.275 --> 1:14:03.943
You haven't
called me that in years.

1:14:06.713 --> 1:14:08.815
No, I guess I haven't.

1:14:14.554 --> 1:14:16.856
Would you like to sit
with me for a little bit?

1:14:19.959 --> 1:14:21.294
I would.

1:14:49.089 --> 1:14:50.857
[clock chiming]

1:14:55.395 --> 1:14:57.097
Well, look at that.

1:14:59.265 --> 1:15:00.500
All right...

1:15:04.437 --> 1:15:06.272
Merry Christmas, Doc.

1:15:11.077 --> 1:15:12.712
Merry Christmas, John.

1:15:29.596 --> 1:15:32.332
WILL: "And as they nuzzle up
in front of the roaring fire,

1:15:32.365 --> 1:15:34.801
"snow falling gently outside,

1:15:34.834 --> 1:15:36.936
"the clock chimes midnight

1:15:36.970 --> 1:15:39.072
and we fade to white."

1:15:39.105 --> 1:15:42.075
"The end."

1:15:42.108 --> 1:15:44.077
And?

1:15:44.077 --> 1:15:46.246
Just under the wire.

1:15:46.279 --> 1:15:48.448
All that's left
is to hit "send."

1:15:48.481 --> 1:15:49.349
Shall we--

1:15:49.382 --> 1:15:50.083
Shall we do it together?

1:15:50.083 --> 1:15:51.418
Yes, please.

1:15:53.119 --> 1:15:54.454
[chuckles]
Okay.

1:15:54.487 --> 1:15:55.722
Thank you so much.

1:15:55.755 --> 1:15:57.157
Thank you so much for
helping me with this.

1:15:57.190 --> 1:15:58.291
Of course.

1:15:58.324 --> 1:16:00.193
We just, like,
completed a miracle.

1:16:00.226 --> 1:16:01.428
Yeah, and you know what?

1:16:01.461 --> 1:16:04.564
We got to spend
Christmas in Salem.

1:16:06.032 --> 1:16:07.734
Even if we couldn't
actually be there in person,

1:16:07.767 --> 1:16:10.170
You know,
writing all that...

1:16:10.203 --> 1:16:11.771
it made me miss it.

1:16:11.805 --> 1:16:12.839
You know?

1:16:12.872 --> 1:16:14.074
Miss them.

1:16:15.141 --> 1:16:16.376
Yeah, me, too.

1:16:17.477 --> 1:16:18.678
We'll have to visit soon.

1:16:21.414 --> 1:16:22.549
Hm.

1:16:22.582 --> 1:16:23.850
It's midnight here, too.

1:16:26.353 --> 1:16:28.254
Merry Christmas, honey.

1:16:28.288 --> 1:16:29.789
Merry Christmas...

1:16:29.823 --> 1:16:30.924
pookie.

1:16:30.957 --> 1:16:31.891
[laughing]

1:16:44.904 --> 1:16:48.441
MERRY CHRISTMAS TO ALL!

1:17:04.124 --> 1:17:04.224
* *
